                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d91">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Wharton</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Mizner</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-09-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 10, 1890</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 170.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your No. 141 of the 18th of August last, in
                    relation to the seizure of the United States consulate in the city of San
                    Salvador by the troops of the Provisional Government during the battle there on
                    the 30th and 31st of July last, has been received.</p>
                <p>The Government of the United States can but appreciate the good disposition of
                    the Provisional Government of Salvador in the steps taken to reinstate the
                    consul in his office as described.</p>
                <p>Consul Myers will be instructed to furnish you with a statement of the damages
                    done to his own property and to that of the consulate; but, in the expectation
                    that due reparation will spontaneously be made for the injuries incurred, a
                    consideration of the otherwise pressing question of securing proper compensation
                    will be deterred.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William F. Wharton</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
